com.acrolinx.javasdk.gui

Enum MarkingType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MarkingType>
      • com.acrolinx.javasdk.gui.MarkingType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<MarkingType>

    public enum MarkingType
extends Enum<MarkingType>
    The enum MarkingType is an enum of all possible types of marking provided by the Acrolinx Java SDK.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      ACTIVE
      The ACTIVE marking the user has clicked on.
      ADMITTED
      an admitted marking
      DEPRECATED
      a deprecated marking
      EXTRACTION_EXCLUDE
      EXTRACTION_EXCLUDE is a marking for excluded text when a check is performed with result type FLAG_EXTRACTION.
      EXTRACTION_INCLUDE
      EXTRACTION_INCLUDE is a marking for included text when a check is performed with result type FLAG_EXTRACTION.
      EXTRACTION_SENTENCE_BREAK
      EXTRACTION_SENTENCE_BREAK is a marking for included text with segmentation level sentence break when a check is performed with result type FLAG_EXTRACTION.
      GRAMMAR
      a GRAMMAR marking
      MULTI
      If Flags are overlapping the MarkingType will be multi.
      NULL
      the Null object of MarkingType

      • getMarkingTypeForFlags

        public static MarkingType getMarkingTypeForFlags(Set<Flag> flags)
        Gets the marking type for flags. If flags.size() > 1 it will be MULTI. If size() == 1 it will be the MarkingType for this Flag. If size() == 0 NULL will be returned.
        Parameters:
        flags - the flags,should not be null
        Returns:
        the marking type for flags
